The paper proposes a novel optimization model for tumor saliency estimation in breast ultrasound images by utilizing breast anatomy. This involves decomposing the image into layers using Neutro-Connectedness and generating foreground and background maps. The approach also integrates adaptive center bias and region-based correlation cues. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Medical Imaging (cs.Medical Imaging), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel objective function, which involves optimization, making it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
